{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SFFdPCf4iq9563LXwqjpAp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The replica set was initialized with only the 2 data-bearing members (`mongo-rs-0`, `mongo-rs-1`). A 2-node set requires both members for a majority (1/2 < majority), so any single node failure makes elections impossible.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Set an explicit cluster-wide write concern (`{w: 1}`) — required by MongoDB 5.0+ before reconfiguring to a PSA (Primary-Secondary-Arbiter) topology.\n2. Added `mongo-arb-0` as an arbiter via `rs.addArb()`.\n\n**Result:**\n- 3 voting members total: 2 data-bearing (votes=1 each) + 1 arbiter (votes=1, `arbiterOnly=true`)\n- Majority quorum = 2, so elections succeed even when one data node is down\n- Arbiter stores no data — zero storage cost increase\n- `app.test` still has all 3 documents — data intact"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":489,"cache_read_input_tokens":34719,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":489},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba980494-6950-453b-a9a0-51f8b609f7aa","uuid":"fb650fca-e14d-4b2b-82f8-5243e2e8d8fc","request_id":"req_011CcLSWUnqkVHuShqwRhfQ9"}
